results.name: Numbers with strictly decreasing prime multiplicities.
link: Charles R Greathouse IV, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
example: 10 = 2*5 has prime multiplicities (1,1) so is not in the sequence.
20 = 2*2*5 has prime multiplicities (2,1) so is in the sequence
90 = 2*3*3*5 has prime multiplicities (1,2,1) so is not in the sequence.
program: (PARI) isok(n) = my(vm = factor(n)[,2]); vm == vecsort(vm,,4) && (#vm == #Set(vm)); \\ _Michel Marcus_, May 17 2018
results.author: _Gus Wiseman_, May 16 2018
